-- FACTBOX: Key facts about U.S. May auto sales
-- 
-- Tue Jun 3, 2008 7:27pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/06/03/us-usa-autosales-idUSN0335539620080603

 

 DETROIT  (Reuters) - May auto sales fell 14 percent from a year earlier on an adjusted basis, according to data from auto manufacturers on Tuesday. The following are highlights from the largest carmakers in the U.S. market. 

 Overall industry * Total light vehicle sales -- 1.397 million units. General Motors Corp ( GM.N ) * Light vehicle sales down adjusted 30 percent (272,363 units), unadjusted sales down 28 percent * Year-to-date sales down 17 percent * Inventories at month-end: 772,000 units, down about 219,000 vehicles from a year earlier * Cars/trucks: Car sales down adjusted 17 percent/light truck sales down 39 percent * Market share: 19.1 percent * Key vehicles: Chevrolet Impala down 35.7 percent, Chevrolet Malibu up 33.9 percent, Chevrolet Silverado down 44.1 percent, Chevrolet Tahoe down 42 percent, GMC Sierra down 33.9 percent. * Incentives: average $3,477 per vehicle, up from $2,996 a year earlier. Toyota Motor Corp ( 7203.T )( TM.N ) * Vehicle sales down adjusted 8 percent (257,404 units), unadjusted sales down percent * Year-to-date sales down adjusted 5 percent * Market share: 18.4 percent * Cars/trucks: Car sales down adjusted 3.3 percent/trucks down 15.5 percent * Key vehicles: Tundra down 34 percent, Camry down 1.5 percent, Prius down 39.8 percent, Corolla up 12.4 percent * Incentives: averaged $1,045 per vehicle, up from $804 a year earlier. Ford Motor Co ( F.N ) * Vehicle sales down 19 percent (217,998 units) on an adjusted basis, unadjusted sales down 16 percent * Year-to-date sales down adjusted 12 percent * Inventories at month-end were 560,000 units, up 6,000 units from a year earlier * Retail/fleet sales: Retail sales of Ford, Lincoln, Mercury up 20 percent on an unadjusted basis/total fleet sales down 30 percent * Cars/trucks: Car sales flat on an adjusted basis/truck sales down 28 percent * Market share: 14.7 percent including Jaguar, Land Rover, Volvo * Key vehicles: F-Series down 30.6 percent on an unadjusted basis, Explorer down 41.2 percent, Expedition down 42.9 percent, Focus up 53.2 percent, Fusion up 26.7 percent. * Incentives: averaged $3,326 per vehicle, up from $2,964 a year earlier. Chrysler LLC * Car and light truck sales down adjusted 28 percent (148,747 units), unadjusted sales down 25 percent * Cars/trucks: Car sales down 31 percent/truck sales down 27 percent on an adjusted basis. * Market share: 10.6 percent * Inventories at month-end were 412,009 units, or a 75-day supply, down 14 percent from year ago. * Key vehicles: Jeep Wrangler down 25 percent, Dodge Ram pickup down 37 percent, Dodge Caliber up 7 percent, all on an unadjusted basis. * Incentives: average $3,714 per vehicle, down from $3,823 a year earlier. Honda Motor Co ( 7267.T )( HMC.N ) * Vehicle sales up an adjusted 11.3 percent (167,997 units), unadjusted sales up 16 percent * Year-to-date sales up an adjusted 3.1 percent * Cars/trucks: cars up 27 percent, trucks down 12 percent * Market share: 12 percent * Key vehicles: Civic up 28.3 percent, Fit up 47.4 percent, Accord up 31.9 percent, Pilot down 19.7 percent, Odyssey down 18.0 percent, CR-V down 1.5 percent * Incentives: average $1,256 per vehicle, down from $1,383 a year earlier Nissan Motor Co Ltd ( 7201.T ) * Car and light truck sales up an adjusted 4.4 percent year over year (100,874 units); up 8 percent unadjusted. * Market share: 7.2 percent * Cars/trucks: Cars up adjusted 14 percent/trucks down 14 percent * Key vehicles: Altima up adjusted 38.3 percent, Versa up 10.6 percent, Sentra up 5.5 percent, Titan down 57.5 percent, Murano down 8.9 percent. * Incentives: average $2,090 per vehicle, up from $1,943 a year earlier. Sources: Autodata Corp and industry tracking firm Edmunds.com for incentives and broad sales and market share comparisons in adjusted terms to account for one more selling day in May compared with a year earlier, and company releases. (Reporting by  Soyoung Kim  and  David Bailey , editing by Richard Chang)